    <p><a href="http://www.box.com/">Box</a>, the enterprise storage and collaboration company, has reportedly filed for an initial public offering of its stock.&nbsp;<a href="http://qz.com/172541/box-has-secretly-filed-for-an-ipo/" target="_blank"><i>Quartz</i></a> and the&nbsp;<a href="http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/01/30/web-storage-firm-box-files-for-ipo/" target="_blank"><i>Wall Street Journal</i></a> are reporting that the company has filed confidential paperwork to go public, under&nbsp;<a href="http://online.wsj.com/article/BT-CO-20130219-705317.html" target="_blank">a provision of the JOBS Act</a> that allows companies with less than $1 billion in annual revenue to prepare to go public in secret.</p>
